fields.name: EnableNonSslPort
fields.description: Specifies whether the non-ssl Redis server port (6379) is enabled.

fields.name: MinimumTlsVersion
fields.description: Optional: requires clients to use a specified TLS version (or higher) to connect (e,g, '1.0', '1.1', '1.2')

fields.name: PublicNetworkAccess
fields.description: Whether or not public endpoint access is allowed for this cache.  Value is optional but if passed in, must be 'Enabled' or 'Disabled'. If 'Disabled', private endpoints are the exclusive access method. Default value is 'Enabled'

fields.name: RedisConfiguration
fields.description: All Redis Settings. Few possible keys: rdb-backup-enabled,rdb-storage-connection-string,rdb-backup-frequency,maxmemory-delta,maxmemory-policy,notify-keyspace-events,maxmemory-samples,slowlog-log-slower-than,slowlog-max-len,list-max-ziplist-entries,list-max-ziplist-value,hash-max-ziplist-entries,hash-max-ziplist-value,set-max-intset-entries,zset-max-ziplist-entries,zset-max-ziplist-value etc.

fields.name: RedisVersion
fields.description: Redis version. This should be in the form 'major[.minor]' (only 'major' is required) or the value 'latest' which refers to the latest stable Redis version that is available. Supported versions: 4.0, 6.0 (latest). Default value is 'latest'.

fields.name: ReplicasPerMaster
fields.description: The number of replicas to be created per primary.

fields.name: ReplicasPerPrimary
fields.description: The number of replicas to be created per primary.

fields.name: ShardCount
fields.description: The number of shards to be created on a Premium Cluster Cache.

fields.name: Sku
fields.description: The SKU of the Redis cache to deploy.
